		<div id="comment_body_64586901"><p>As of the iPhone 7, removing the battery required removing the glued-on case, not trivial, but not difficult, and then removing the adhesive strips.</p><p>If you are lucky and know the trick, removing the adhesive strips wasn't terribly difficult.  There is a tab you can lift with tweezers and pulling it longitudinally pops it off cleanly.  If you do it wrong, you need a small 3d-printable tool to cut through the adhesive with fishing line.</p><p>If I were me, I'd prefer they make it easier to open the cases far more than making the battery have some zappy whiz-bang tech to pull the battery.</p></div>
